article_metadata.description: WHITESVILLE  Fillmore got off to a red-hot start and never cooled off.Jordan Mullen hit five of Fillmore's eight 3-pointers and finished with a game-high 25 points in a 77-71 win over Whitesville on Friday.Kyle Redman had 17 points, while Jordan Crouch had 13, and Bjorn Webb added 10 for Fillmore (10-2)."I told the guys at halftime that we came out too soft," said Whitesville coach Doug VanSkiver.
